# Cursor Rules for Context7 Integration

## Auto-trigger Context7 for code-related questions
When the user asks about:
- Code examples or implementation
- Library documentation or API usage
- Setup or configuration steps
- Framework-specific questions
- Authentication or database queries

Automatically use Context7 tools to provide up-to-date documentation and examples.

## Library-specific triggers
When users mention specific libraries or frameworks, use the appropriate Context7 library ID:
- React → /react/docs
- Next.js → /vercel/next.js
- Supabase → /supabase/supabase
- MongoDB → /mongodb/docs
- And others as needed

## Always provide practical examples
When using Context7 documentation, include:
- Working code snippets
- Step-by-step implementation
- Best practices from the official docs
- Real-world usage patterns






